otherNames><gtr:surname>Steeples</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=RES-173-27-0084"><gtr:id>5BD206E1-4F98-4192-ACB9-26DB6015B182</gtr:id><gtr:title>The Goverance of Cities and City Regions: Clarifying the Evidence for its Importance for Economic Development</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>RES-173-27-0084</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>The project will examine the current policy literature on the governance and responsibilities of cities and city-regions and the evidence adduced to support the benefits of particular governance systems for economic development. For example, it is often stated that city-region performance in the UK would be improved by a mayoral system, but the evidence for this is largely anecdotal. A second phase will identify key questions which seem significant in policy terms where the evidence base appears problematic. It will be taken forward through an initial review of the policy and research literature, guided by interviews with key researchers and policy-makers. A matrix or typology will be developed for the key policy issues and the evidence supporting them. In the second phase, this would be used to prompt discussions with the policy and academic community on the issues raised and areas where further research would be useful. A report of this work will be produced and published in an academic journal.
